members.name: AbstractBatchRenderer
members.brief: Renderer dedicated to drawing and batching sprites.
members.description: This is the default batch renderer. It buffers objects with texture-based geometries and renders them in batches. It uploads multiple textures to the GPU to reduce to the number of draw calls.

members.name: _drawCallPool
members.description:
Pool of BatchDrawCall objects that flush used to create "batches" of the objects being rendered.

These are never re-allocated again. Shared between all batch renderers because it can be only one "flush" working at the moment.

members.name: _textureArrayPool
members.description:
Pool of BatchDrawCall objects that flush used to create "batches" of the objects being rendered.

These are never re-allocated again. Shared between all batch renderers because it can be only one "flush" working at the moment.

members.name: MAX_TEXTURES
members.description: Maximum number of textures that can be uploaded to the GPU under the current context. It is initialized properly in this.contextChange.

members.name: renderer
members.brief: The renderer this manager works for.

members.name: size
members.description: The number of bufferable objects before a flush occurs automatically.

members.name: state
members.brief: The WebGL state in which this renderer will work.

members.name: vertexSize
members.description:
Size of data being buffered per vertex in the attribute buffers (in floats). By default, the batch-renderer plugin uses 6:

aVertexPosition 2
aTextureCoords 2
aColor 1
aTextureId 1

members.name: _shader
members.brief: This shader is generated by this.shaderGenerator.
members.description: It is generated specifically to handle the required number of textures being batched together.

members.name: geometryClass
members.description: The class that represents the geometry of objects that are going to be batched with this.

members.name: shaderGenerator
members.description:
This is used to generate a shader that can color each vertex based on a aTextureId attribute that points to an texture in uSampler.

This enables the objects with different textures to be drawn in the same draw call.

You can customize your shader by creating your custom shader generator.

members.name: _aBuffers
members.description:
Pool of ViewableBuffer objects that are sorted in order of increasing size. The flush method uses the buffer with the least size above the amount it requires. These are used for passing attributes.

The first buffer has a size of 8; each subsequent buffer has double capacity of its previous.

members.name: _bufferedElements
members.brief: Buffer of objects that are yet to be rendered.

members.name: _bufferedTextures
members.description: Data for texture batch builder, helps to save a bit of CPU on a pass

members.name: _bufferSize
members.description: Number of elements that are buffered and are waiting to be flushed.

members.name: _flushId
members.description:
A flush may occur multiple times in a single frame. On iOS devices or when settings.CAN_UPLOAD_SAME_BUFFER is false, the batch renderer does not upload data to the same WebGLBuffer for performance reasons.

This is the index into packedGeometries that points to geometry holding the most recent buffers.

members.name: _iBuffers
members.description:
Pool of Uint16Array objects that are sorted in order of increasing size. The flush method uses the buffer with the least size above the amount it requires. These are used for passing indices.

The first buffer has a size of 12; each subsequent buffer has double capacity of its previous.

members.name: _indexCount
members.description: Total count of all indices used by the currently buffered objects.

members.name: _packedGeometries
members.description:
Pool of this.geometryClass geometry objects that store buffers. They are used to pass data to the shader on each draw call.

These are never re-allocated again, unless a context change occurs; however, the pool may be expanded if required.

members.name: _packedGeometryPoolSize
members.description: Size of this._packedGeometries. It can be expanded if more than this._packedGeometryPoolSize flushes occur in a single frame.

members.name: _vertexCount
members.description: Total count of all vertices used by the currently buffered objects.

members.name: packInterleavedGeometry
members.description:
Takes the four batching parameters of element, interleaves and pushes them into the batching attribute/index buffers given.

It uses these properties: vertexData uvs, textureId and indicies. It also uses the "tint" of the base-texture, if present.

car.installComponent("interior", new AirConditioner());

car.drop("1234 Virtual Street, OH, Virtual US", "Universe-Default");

car.accelerate(2).until(65).then(0);
